1. Trump: Extend the promotion of stablecoin legislation to August;
2. US Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent: We will end the regulatory crackdown on crypto assets;
3. Trump: In the future, the government's crypto assets will be stored in a new US digital asset library;
4. Trump plans to "revoke and modify" US crypto tax rules;
5. Trump reiterated that he will not use taxpayer funds to acquire digital assets;
6. The White House: The United States will begin auditing existing cryptocurrency holdings;
7. Fed Powell: No rush to cut interest rates before the impact of Trump's policies becomes clearer;
8. Crypto exchange Gemini has submitted IPO applications to Goldman Sachs and Citigroup;
9. Eugene: ETH short positions have been closed, and ENA band long positions are still held;
10. Coinbase adds Aethir (ATH) and Syrup (SYRUP) to the coin listing roadmap;
11. Binance issued a statement on the "large short positions" before the GPS announcement: no abnormal transactions;
12. There are currently 11 The lawsuits and investigations of crypto companies/individuals were dismissed or suspended by the US SEC;
13. The US unemployment rate in February was 4.1%, the highest since November 2024.
